subsection.def:
auction
                    (拍賣), in relation to a lot, means the auction
                of the lot pursuant to section 5(1)(a);

Cap. 17A (《第17A章》) means the
                Lands Tribunal Rules (Cap. 17 sub. leg. A);
                    (Added 25 of 2024 s. 3)

directions
                    (指示) means directions under section
                    4(6);

paragraph.content:
includes any person who becomes a successor in title to any such person
                        or persons at any time before a purchaser of the lot becomes the owner of
                        the lot where the lot is the subject of an order for sale;

includes any person who becomes a successor in title to any such person
                        or persons at any time before a purchaser of the lot becomes the owner of
                        the lot where the lot is the subject of an order for sale;

subsection.def:
mortgage
                    (按揭) means a security over a lot (including
                an undivided share in a lot) for securing money or money’s worth;

mortgagee
                    (承按人) includes any person claiming under a
                mortgagee but does not include a mortgagee in possession;

occupation permit (佔用許可證) means an occupation permit issued by the Building Authority under
                    section 21(2)(a) of Cap. 123;
                    (Added 25 of 2024 s. 3)

redevelopment
                    (重新發展), in relation to a lot, means the
                replacement of a building on (or formerly on) the lot;

paragraph.continued:
a mortgagee in possession of any property on a lot shall be deemed to be
                    the owner of the undivided shares in the lot which relate to that
                    property;

subparagraph.content:
if more than one additional lot is covered—at least one of the
                        additional lots adjoins a set of staircase-connected lots along a common
                        boundary;

paragraph.content:
the percentage of the undivided shares owned by the majority owner in the
                    additional lot, or each of the additional lots, is not less than 65%;
                    and

a Government lease that shows the area or boundary of the lot, together
                    with any document subsequently executed or issued by the Government that effects
                    an adjustment of the area or boundary of the lot;

paragraph.continued:
together with any document subsequently executed or issued by the
                    Government that effects an adjustment of the area or boundary of the lot;
                    and

paragraph.content:
cause a copy of the application to be registered under the Land
                    Registration Ordinance (Cap. 128) against the lot;
                    and

subsection.def:
Cap. 545A (《第545A章》) means the
                Land (Compulsory Sale for Redevelopment) (Specification of Lower Percentage) Notice
                    (Cap. 545 sub. leg. A);

subparagraph.content:
if any minority owner of the lot the subject of the application
                        disputes the value of any property as assessed in the application, hearing
                        and determining the dispute;

making an order that all the undivided shares in the lot the subject of
                        the application be sold for the purposes of the redevelopment of the lot;
                        or

that the Tribunal has made an order that all the undivided shares
                            in the lot be sold for the purposes of the redevelopment of the lot;
                            and

the sale and purchase of the lot the subject of the order, including
                        (but without limiting the generality of the foregoing) settling the
                        particulars and conditions of sale of the lot;

the holding by the trustees of such part of those proceeds as is
                            specified by the Tribunal in view of any lis pendens affecting the lot;
                            and

the payment of that part of those proceeds, upon the occurrence of
                            an event specified by the Tribunal, to such person or persons as is or
                            are specified by the Tribunal;

paragraph.content:
an order for sale was made for the lots the subject of an application that
                    covers 2 or more lots by reason of section 3(2)(c) or (d) or (2A);
                    and

each of the buildings (whether wholly or partly) erected on the subject
                    lots under the redevelopment has been issued with an occupation
                    permit;

the carrying out of building works following any refusal to give approval
                    or to consent under subsection (5)(a) or withdrawal of approval under
                    subsection (5)(b);

subsection.def:
lease
                    (租契) includes every agreement for the letting
                of any premises, whether oral or in writing, and howsoever described;

subparagraph.content:
by a person who would have been entitled, or who appears would have
                        been entitled, to be paid the residue if the residue had remained with the
                        Tribunal;

paragraph.content:
if Part II of the New Territories Ordinance (Cap.
                            97) applies to the lot, any Chinese custom or customary right
                        affecting the land;

subparagraph.content:
there has been a dispute referred to in section
                                4(1)(a)(i) that has resulted in a variation of those values;
